Hi @vidartf and others,

I’m attempting to use the CellDiffWidget inside the Git extension and am running into a layout issue. 
When I plainly use new CellDiffWidget, layout of the line number, source code, and the line number background is off [1]. 
From what I can tell, this is mostly affected by these two styles. When I manually add these using developer tools, it looks better

```
.CodeMirror-gutter.CodeMirror-linenumbers {
  width: 29px;
}

.CodeMirror-sizer {
  margin-left: 47px;
}
```
I’m not sure where these inline styles are being added on these CodeMirror DOM elements. Hoping you have some pointers around how to effectively layout this widget. LMK if you need more info. Thanks!

[1]
![nbdime-gitext](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43826141/60774409-882c0380-a0c8-11e9-8173-657703de2617.png)

[2] NBDime Lab Extension
![nbdime-labext](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43826141/60774417-95e18900-a0c8-11e9-8efc-3dc5eb2021a4.png)

**Problem: using nbdime-1.0.0 I have trouble telling it to ignore all diffs but code cells when run via notebook.**

1) first the docs are broken:

http://nbdime.readthedocs.io/en/stable/config.html

the given examples fail to validate via `nbdime --config` - True/False have to be true/false to validate.

2) second it doesn't seem like there is any validation to what user config file includes, you can write anything that's valid json format and it'll use it. You have no way of telling whether you are doing it right or not.

3) I tried many many many different combinations to get my custom configured nbdime to work as an extension from jupyter notebook, but my configuration is completely ignored.

What I'm trying to configure is for it to ignore all attachments, outputs and metadata, I tried many versions of `~/.jupyter/nbdime_config.json`. The latest incarnation is:

```
{
  "GitDiff": {
    "Ignore": {
      "/cells/*/outputs": true,
      "/cells/*/attachments": true,
      "/cells/*/metadata": true
    }
  },
  "Diff": {
    "Ignore": {
      "/cells/*/outputs": true,
      "/cells/*/attachments": true,
      "/cells/*/metadata": true
    }
  },
  "WebTool": {
    "Ignore": {
      "/cells/*/outputs": true,
      "/cells/*/attachments": true,
      "/cells/*/metadata": true
    }
  },
  "Web": {
    "Ignore": {
      "/cells/*/outputs": true,
      "/cells/*/attachments": true,
      "/cells/*/metadata": true
    }
  }
}

```

I also tried setting:

`"ignore_transients": true`

to no avail.

I can see that nbdime picks my changes via `nbdime --config`

But when I run `http://localhost:8888/nbdime/git-difftool?base=test.ipynb` invoked via the git diff button in the notebook. I get all the diffs. I want just the code cell diffs.

Thank you.

nbdime-1.0.0
